---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Temporary Resident Visa Insurance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'quick-comparison', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'geoblue', text: 'GeoBlue', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img-global', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing for Applicants', level: 2 },
  { id: 'mexico-network', text: 'Mexico Network Access', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Recommendation', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { text: 'Mexico Seniors Insurance', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/mexico' },
  { text: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { text: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
];

const quickCompareColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const quickCompareRows = [
  { feature: 'Mexico Network', cigna: 'Excellent', geoblue: 'Good (reimbursement)', img: 'Good (reimbursement)' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', cigna: 'Add-on available', geoblue: 'Full BCBS network', img: 'Available' },
  { feature: 'Max Entry Age', cigna: '74', geoblue: '74', img: '74' },
  { feature: 'Monthly Cost (65yo)', cigna: '$350-450', geoblue: '$450-600', img: '$280-380' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing Mexico', cigna: 'Extensive', geoblue: 'Limited', img: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Mexico + convenience', geoblue: 'US expats, US care access', img: 'Budget + flexibility' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'benefit', header: 'Benefit' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { benefit: 'Inpatient/Hospital', cigna: 'Unlimited', geoblue: '$5-8M', img: '$1-8M (plan dependent)' },
  { benefit: 'Outpatient Care', cigna: 'Full coverage', geoblue: 'Full coverage', img: 'Full coverage' },
  { benefit: 'US Treatment', cigna: 'Add-on', geoblue: 'Included (key benefit)', img: 'Add-on' },
  { benefit: 'Emergency Evacuation', cigna: '$1M', geoblue: 'Included', img: '$500K-1M' },
  { benefit: 'Pre-existing', cigna: 'Underwriting', geoblue: 'Underwriting', img: 'Underwriting/Moratorium' },
  { benefit: 'Prescription Drugs', cigna: 'Included', geoblue: 'Included', img: 'Included' },
  { benefit: 'Mental Health', cigna: 'Standard', geoblue: 'Good', img: 'Limited' },
  { benefit: 'Dental', cigna: 'Optional', geoblue: 'Optional', img: 'Optional' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Individual, Age 55', cigna: '$260-330/mo', geoblue: '$350-450/mo', img: '$200-270/mo' },
  { profile: 'Individual, Age 65', cigna: '$350-450/mo', geoblue: '$450-600/mo', img: '$280-380/mo' },
  { profile: 'Individual, Age 70', cigna: '$450-570/mo', geoblue: '$580-750/mo', img: '$360-480/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 60', cigna: '$540-680/mo', geoblue: '$700-900/mo', img: '$420-560/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 65', cigna: '$700-900/mo', geoblue: '$900-1200/mo', img: '$560-760/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Mexico Temporary Resident Visa: Cigna vs GeoBlue vs IMG | 2025"
  description="Compare the best health insurance for Mexico temporary resident visa. Cigna Global vs GeoBlue vs IMG Global - coverage, US access, pricing, and which to choose."
  headline="Best Health Insurance for Mexico Temporary Resident Visa"
  subheadline="Cigna Global vs GeoBlue vs IMG Global: Finding the right balance of Mexico coverage and US access"
  heroImage="/images/countries/mexico-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
>
  <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Temporary Resident Visa Insurance</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Mexico's Temporary Resident Visa (Residente Temporal) doesn't officially require health insurance, but having quality coverage is essential. Mexican private healthcare is excellent in major cities, but for many American retirees, maintaining access to US healthcare—whether for specialists, family emergencies, or peace of mind—is equally important.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Why Insurance Matters in Mexico</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li><strong>No Medicare abroad:</strong> Medicare doesn't cover you in Mexico</li>
        <li><strong>Quality private care:</strong> Best Mexican hospitals rival US standards</li>
        <li><strong>US proximity:</strong> San Diego, Houston, Phoenix are hours away</li>
        <li><strong>Cost without insurance:</strong> Even affordable Mexican care adds up</li>
        <li><strong>IMSS limitations:</strong> Public system has long waits and quality varies</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The key decision for Mexico is US coverage. Unlike European retirees, Americans often maintain strong ties north of the border—family, existing doctors, specialists they trust. GeoBlue's Blue Cross Blue Shield network makes US care seamless. Cigna offers strong Mexico networks with US as an add-on. IMG provides budget-friendly coverage with flexible options.
    </p>
    <p>
      For Americans, proximity to the US border changes the calculation. Living in Baja, you're 30 minutes from San Diego hospitals. In Puerto Vallarta, Houston is a 2-hour flight. This accessibility means US coverage isn't just for emergencies—it can be part of your regular healthcare strategy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="quick-comparison" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Comparison</h2>

    <ComparisonTable columns={quickCompareColumns} rows={quickCompareRows} />

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Best Mexico Network</p>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700">Cigna Global</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <p class="font-semibold text-indigo-900">Best US Access</p>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-700">GeoBlue</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <p class="font-semibold text-green-900">Best Value</p>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700">IMG Global</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Mexico Insurance Quotes"
    description="Compare personalized quotes with US coverage options. Takes 5 minutes, no commitment."
    buttonText="Compare Quotes Now"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <section id="cigna-global" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Cigna Global for Mexico</h2>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Strengths</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-neutral-600">
            <li>✓ Best direct billing network in Mexico</li>
            <li>✓ Major hospitals: Hospital Ángeles, Christus Muguerza, ABC</li>
            <li>✓ US coverage available as add-on</li>
            <li>✓ 24/7 English support</li>
            <li>✓ Excellent app and digital tools</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Considerations</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-neutral-600">
            <li>• US add-on increases cost 30-40%</li>
            <li>• Higher base price than IMG</li>
            <li>• US network less seamless than GeoBlue</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Cigna Global offers the best Mexico network experience. Direct billing at Hospital Ángeles (Mexico's premier private hospital chain), Christus Muguerza, Hospital ABC, and major facilities in every popular expat destination. Walk in, show your card, get treated without upfront payment.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      For Americans who want excellent Mexico coverage with the option to access US care, Cigna's approach works well. Add US coverage when you need it (visiting family, accessing specific specialists), keep it off when you don't. The flexibility has value.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Best for:</strong> Expats wanting seamless Mexico hospital access, those who value direct billing convenience, and Americans who want optional (not mandatory) US coverage.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-primary-700 transition" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="geoblue" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">GeoBlue for Mexico</h2>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Strengths</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-neutral-600">
            <li>✓ Full Blue Cross Blue Shield US network</li>
            <li>✓ Seamless US care access</li>
            <li>✓ Ideal for Americans with US ties</li>
            <li>✓ Strong prescription coverage</li>
            <li>✓ Good mental health benefits</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Considerations</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-neutral-600">
            <li>• Higher premiums (US coverage built in)</li>
            <li>• Mexico coverage via reimbursement mostly</li>
            <li>• Less direct billing in Mexico</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      GeoBlue is purpose-built for American expats who want full US healthcare access while living abroad. Their Blue Cross Blue Shield network access means you can see US doctors, visit US hospitals, and fill prescriptions at US pharmacies as if you never left—no surprise bills, no out-of-network headaches.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      For Mexico specifically, this matters because of proximity. Living in San Miguel de Allende? Houston specialists are a short flight away. In Los Cabos? San Diego hospitals are closer than Mexico City. GeoBlue makes using US healthcare strategic rather than emergency-only.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The trade-off is Mexico coverage works primarily through reimbursement. You pay Mexican providers and file for reimbursement—not difficult, but less convenient than Cigna's direct billing. For routine Mexico care, this is manageable. For major hospitalizations, GeoBlue can often arrange direct payment.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Best for:</strong> American expats who want seamless US care access, those who'll use US specialists regularly, anyone who values BCBS network access, and expats near the US border.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <a href="/get-quotes" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-primary-700 transition" style="color: white !important;">Get GeoBlue Quote →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="img-global" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">IMG Global for Mexico</h2>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Strengths</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-neutral-600">
            <li>✓ Most affordable option (20-30% less)</li>
            <li>✓ Flexible plan customization</li>
            <li>✓ Good comprehensive coverage</li>
            <li>✓ US coverage available</li>
            <li>✓ Moratorium underwriting option (faster approval)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Considerations</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-neutral-600">
            <li>• Mostly reimbursement model in Mexico</li>
            <li>• Smaller company than Cigna</li>
            <li>• Mental health coverage more limited</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      IMG Global (Global Medical Insurance) offers the best value for Mexico expats willing to handle reimbursement claims. Their premiums run 20-30% below Cigna and significantly below GeoBlue, with comprehensive coverage that meets most expats' needs.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The reimbursement model works well in Mexico because healthcare costs are lower. Pay $200 for a specialist visit, file electronically, get reimbursed in 5-10 days. It's not as convenient as direct billing, but the premium savings over 10+ years of retirement are substantial.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious expats, those comfortable with reimbursement model, anyone prioritizing value over convenience, and expats who won't need US care regularly.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-primary-700 transition" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="coverage-comparison" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Coverage Comparison</h2>

    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">The US Coverage Question</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The biggest difference between these providers is US coverage approach. GeoBlue includes full US coverage as a core benefit—you're paying for it whether you use it or not, but it's seamless when you do. Cigna and IMG offer US coverage as add-ons, letting you control costs if you won't use US care regularly.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Calculate your likely US usage:</strong> If you'll visit family, see US specialists, or want US care as a serious option, GeoBlue or Cigna+US make sense. If Mexico will be your primary healthcare location with US visits rare, IMG or Cigna without US coverage saves money.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="pricing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Pricing for Mexico Temporary Residents</h2>

    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />

    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">
      *GeoBlue prices include US coverage. Cigna and IMG prices are for Americas excluding US; add 30-40% for US coverage.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="mexico-network" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Mexico Network Access</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Mexico City</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm"><strong>Cigna direct billing:</strong> Hospital ABC, Hospital Ángeles, Médica Sur, Hospital Español</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm"><strong>GeoBlue/IMG:</strong> Same hospitals via reimbursement</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Guadalajara</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm"><strong>Cigna direct billing:</strong> Hospital Ángeles, Hospital Country 2000, Christus Muguerza</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">San Miguel de Allende / Guanajuato</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm"><strong>All providers:</strong> Limited local options; Querétaro and León hospitals (1-2 hours) for major care</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Consider: US coverage valuable for complex care given smaller local market</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Puerto Vallarta / Riviera Nayarit</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm"><strong>Cigna direct billing:</strong> Hospital CMQ, San Javier Marina Hospital</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Guadalajara (4-5 hours) or US for complex procedures</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Los Cabos / Baja</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm"><strong>All providers:</strong> BlueNet Hospital Cabo, Hospital de los Cabos</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">San Diego hospitals (2-3 hours from Tijuana) often preferred for major procedures</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Scenario 1: Cardiac Event in Puerto Vallarta</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">You experience chest pain at home in Puerto Vallarta. Need emergency cardiac care.</p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Cigna:</p>
            <p class="text-blue-800">Direct billing at CMQ or San Javier. Emergency stabilization, then transfer to Guadalajara or US if needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-indigo-900">GeoBlue:</p>
            <p class="text-indigo-800">Emergency care covered. Option to evacuate to Houston for cardiac intervention—covered under US benefits.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-green-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-green-900">IMG:</p>
            <p class="text-green-800">Emergency covered via reimbursement. Evacuation to US or Guadalajara covered if medically necessary.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Scenario 2: Ongoing Cancer Treatment</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">Diagnosed with breast cancer. Need surgery, chemotherapy, and long-term follow-up.</p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Cigna:</p>
            <p class="text-blue-800">Full treatment at Mexican oncology centers covered. MD Anderson in Houston available with US add-on.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-indigo-900">GeoBlue:</p>
            <p class="text-indigo-800">Can choose Mexico treatment or US treatment. MD Anderson, Memorial Sloan Kettering all in-network through BCBS.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-green-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-green-900">IMG:</p>
            <p class="text-green-800">Mexico treatment covered. US treatment requires US add-on. Reimbursement model for all.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-indigo-700 font-medium mt-3">For major cancer treatment, GeoBlue's seamless US access provides most options.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Scenario 3: Visiting Grandchildren in Phoenix</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">During a month-long visit to see family in Phoenix, you need emergency surgery.</p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Cigna + US:</p>
            <p class="text-blue-800">If US coverage added, surgery covered. Without US add-on, emergency only—may face significant costs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-indigo-900">GeoBlue:</p>
            <p class="text-indigo-800">Full BCBS network coverage. Surgery at Banner or Mayo Clinic Phoenix fully covered. This is GeoBlue's strength.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-green-50 p-3 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-green-900">IMG + US:</p>
            <p class="text-green-800">If US coverage added, covered via reimbursement. Without US add-on, limited to emergency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="verdict" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Our Recommendation</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-300 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>• Mexico network convenience matters</li>
          <li>• You want optional US coverage</li>
          <li>• Digital tools are important</li>
          <li>• You dislike reimbursement paperwork</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-indigo-50 border-2 border-indigo-300 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-indigo-900 mb-2">Choose GeoBlue If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-indigo-800">
          <li>• US healthcare access is essential</li>
          <li>• You'll visit the US regularly</li>
          <li>• You want US specialists available</li>
          <li>• You live near the US border</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <a href="/get-quotes" class="inline-block bg-indigo-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded font-semibold hover:bg-indigo-700 transition" style="color: white !important;">Get GeoBlue Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-900 mb-2">Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Budget is your priority</li>
          <li>• You're comfortable with reimbursement</li>
          <li>• Mexico will be primary healthcare</li>
          <li>• US visits are rare</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded font-semibold hover:bg-green-700 transition" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">For Most American Expats: GeoBlue</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        For Americans moving to Mexico, <strong>GeoBlue</strong> offers unique value: full Blue Cross Blue Shield network access means US care is always available, not just for emergencies. Given Mexico's proximity to the US, this flexibility has real practical value.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-3">
        However, if you're committed to using Mexican healthcare primarily, <strong>Cigna Global</strong> provides better Mexico network convenience at lower cost. And if budget matters most, <strong>IMG Global</strong> delivers solid coverage at 20-30% savings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Move to Mexico?"
    description="Get personalized quotes from all providers. Compare real pricing for your Mexican retirement insurance."
    buttonText="Compare All Options"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <section id="faqs" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">FAQs: Mexico Temporary Resident Insurance</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is health insurance required for Mexico temporary resident visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">
          No, Mexico doesn't officially require health insurance for the Residente Temporal visa. However, being uninsured in Mexico means paying out-of-pocket for all care and having no coverage during US visits. Given that Medicare doesn't work abroad, insurance is effectively necessary for most American retirees.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about IMSS (Mexican social security)?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">
          Foreigners with Residente Temporal status can enroll in IMSS voluntarily for about $500-600/year. It's extremely affordable but has limitations: long waits, Spanish-only, quality varies by location. Many expats use IMSS for prescriptions and routine care while maintaining private insurance for serious illness and English-speaking care.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Should I keep Medicare Part B?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">
          It depends on your plans. Medicare Part B costs ~$175/month (2025) and only covers US care. If you'll visit the US regularly and might return eventually, maintaining Part B preserves coverage without late enrollment penalties. If Mexico is permanent and you have international insurance with US coverage, dropping Part B saves money.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Mexican healthcare really good?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">
          Private Mexican healthcare in major cities is excellent—often comparable to US hospitals at 30-50% of the cost. Hospital ABC and Hospital Ángeles in Mexico City, Christus Muguerza in Monterrey, and facilities in Guadalajara are all highly regarded. Many doctors trained in the US and speak English. Rural areas and public hospitals are a different story.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
